# Project: relagarden-astro (Astro v4+)

## Technical Stack
- Framework: Astro
- Language: TypeScript (Strict mode)
- Styling: Tailwind CSS
- Components: Astro Components (.astro) preferred

## Coding Rules
- Use Functional Components for any React/UI logic.
- Keep `.astro` files clean: separate Logic (frontmatter) and Template.
- Prioritize Astro's native components.
- Image optimization: Always use the `<Image />` component from `astro:assets`.

## Content Collections (Cases) Rules
- New case studies MUST be created in `src/content/cases/`.
- Every case study MUST include these frontmatter fields:
  - `title`, `description`, `pubDate` (YYYY-MM-DD)
  - `image` (After image path), `beforeImage` (Before image path)
  - `area`, `cost`, `period`, `tags`
  - `beforeConcerns`: User's pain points before construction (for blue post-it).
  - `customerVoice`: User's feedback after construction (for yellow post-it).
  - `constructionPoints`: An array of 3 technical highlights (for info cards).
- Use Markdown for the main story section. Use **bold** for markers and lists for checkmarks.

## Directory Structure
- `src/components/`: Reusable UI elements.
- `src/layouts/`: Base HTML templates.
- `src/pages/`: File-based routing.
- `src/content/`: Content Collections for Markdown/MDX.

## Naming Conventions
- Components: PascalCase
- Content Files: kebab-case (e.g., 001-okazaki-case.md)